 take the reader to locations which include both the post-Soviet states, specifically Ukraine, Estonia, Latvia and Belarus, and the countries of the traditional 'West' - Italy, the US and Israel.A thought-provoking and engaging book, it is essential reading for advanced students and specialists in Russian and Eastern European Studies, Post-Soviet Studies, Language Studies and Sociolinguistics.Key FeaturesProvides a sociolinguistic perspective on the position of the Russian language throughout the worldDiscusses the globalisation of Russian in metropolitan and non-metropolitan spacesContributes to the understanding of developments in Russian as it engages with different new social, political, geographical, legal and cultural environments"  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aRussian languagexFormer Soviet republics. 0aRussian languagezFormer Soviet republics. 4aLanguage & Linguistics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aAndrews, David R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerdicevskis, Aleksandrs, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBowring, Bill, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEhala, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKulyk, Volodymyr, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNewcity, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPerotto, Monica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRyazanova-Clarke, Lara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWoolhiser, Curt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZabrodskaja, Anastassia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZbenovich